Rating: 4
This was a memorable meal. Spectacular combo of flavours. Would use less avocado next time (my two avocados yielded quite a bit of avocado). Was able to find fresh sweet tamarind (pods) in a box. Simply shelled pods, then boiled in water until flesh fell off the seeds, then pushed it through sieve. Ended up with about 3/4 cup of pulp. Used this in place of the 1/2 cup boiling water and 1/4 cup pulp block required in recipe. Worked well. Will definately make this again.

