Rating: 3
This was very good. I went to 3 stores and called even more but they did not carry the tamarind pulp in a brick. In fact few had even heard of it. I managed to drive nearly every grocery clerk in my town nuts and finally found the tamarind in 2 stores in pod form. I figured out what the heck as I had all ingredients by then. I found the recipe for TAMARIND RECADO here and took it from there. For what its worth the seeds do not drop off the fruit as that recipe says. In any case I broke the pods boiled the fruit, squeezed out the seeds and got a good deal of the pulp, and a pretty big mess. I stayed with it and wow what flavors! I had no idea how much of the stuff I was supposed to have, but it looked like a half cup and tasted darn good when mixed with the other ingredients so I added another bit of each (except sugar) and again it worked. This was great over the jasmine rice. I ended up just eating the avocadoes, toppings and sauce and pushing the shrimp away. My only complaint is that it was too hot with 2 of the Thai chilies and I would cut down on them. I really enjoyed this otherwise and presentation was beautiful.

